DENVER (AP) — Goaltender David Rittich will start Game 1 for the Nashville Predators with starter  Juuse Saros sidelined by a lower-body injury.Predators coach John Hynes announced the decision Tuesday, hours before their first-round series opener against the top-seeded Colorado Avalanche.Saros is out for at least the first two games of the series after leaving a contest last Tuesday favoring his left leg. Saros won 38 games for the Predators this season.The 29-year-old Rittich got the start over Connor Ingram, who’s appeared in just three NHL games. Rittich was the winner when the Predators beat the Avalanche in a shootout last week at Ball Arena. He went 6-3-4 this season for Nashville.“He’s experienced. He’s played more games in the league,” Hynes said. “We trust him and believe in him.”ADVERTISEMENTThis will be the second career playoff appearance for Rittich, who entered for Calgary during Game 6 of a first-round series against Dallas in 2020. Colorado forward Nazem Kadri remains a game-time decision as he deals with an illness.___More AP NHL coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/NHL and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports